***REMOVED*** =============================================================================
***REMOVED*** Residency Scheduler - Environment Configuration
***REMOVED*** =============================================================================
***REMOVED*** Copy this file to .env and fill in your values
***REMOVED*** NEVER commit .env to version control
***REMOVED*** =============================================================================

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Database Configuration
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** PostgreSQL password for the scheduler user
***REMOVED*** Use a strong, unique password in production
DB_PASSWORD=your_secure_database_password_here

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Security Configuration
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Secret key for JWT token signing
***REMOVED*** Generate with: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(64))"
***REMOVED*** CRITICAL: Use a unique, random value in production
SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key_here_generate_a_random_64_char_string

***REMOVED*** Webhook secret for validating incoming webhook requests
***REMOVED*** Generate with: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(64))"
***REMOVED*** CRITICAL: Use a unique, random value in production (minimum 32 characters)
WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret_here_generate_a_random_64_char_string

***REMOVED*** Redis password for authentication
***REMOVED*** Generate with: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"
***REMOVED*** For development: defaults to 'dev_only_password' if not set
***REMOVED*** For production: MUST be set to a strong random value
REDIS_PASSWORD=your_redis_password_here_generate_a_random_string

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Application Configuration
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Debug mode - set to false in production
***REMOVED*** Enables detailed error messages and hot reload in development
DEBUG=true

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** CORS Configuration
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Allowed origins for cross-origin requests
***REMOVED*** In production, set to your actual frontend domain
***REMOVED*** Format: JSON array of strings
CORS_ORIGINS=["http://localhost:3000"]

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Frontend Configuration
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Backend API URL that the frontend will use
***REMOVED*** In production, use your actual backend domain/IP
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Optional: PostgreSQL Direct Connection (for local development)
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Full database URL (usually constructed automatically in docker-compose)
***REMOVED*** DATABASE_URL=postgresql://scheduler:your_password@localhost:5432/residency_scheduler
